flowRoot.flowPara: Dropdown Lists
Widget for selecting an option from a list, intended as a modern replacement for comboboxes.
Short simple list
Long list
If there are more options than can be displayed, the list scrolls. Question: should the selected option would be visible when the list is opened?
Long list with search
Search is an optional feature which can be enabled by developers.
Short list with icons and descriptions
Each option must have a title. Optionally, it can also have an icon and description. Only the icon and title are shown in the button.
This example shows how the list can be wider than the button, if it is necessary to show the options.
Where options with icons and descriptions could be used:
• Display settings: orientation
• Sound settings: input and output device
• Power settings: power button options (to describe what each option does)
• Software: app source dropdown
What's not included here:
• Adding a custom option
• Grouping options in the list
• Allow selecting multiple items
Some of these things could be added at a later date, but it's probably worth waiting until compelling use cases emerge.
When the button is pressed, the list appears below it. The list stays open until the user clicks a row, the button, or outside the list.
If there's not much space below the button, the list should probably be placed above it, and if that's not possible, it should probably obscure it (work needed).
The selected option is indicated by the row background. The row background also changes color on hover.
